Now let me analyze each fix:

**Fix 1 (Line 18)**: `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}` — The value `plain` exists in both old and new type unions. The only change is that `stateful` was added as a new option. No code change needed since `plain` is still valid.

**Fix 2 (Line 15)**: The `<Button>` on lines 15-24 contains only an icon child (`<CheckIcon />`). Per the migration rule, the icon should be moved to the `icon` prop and the element made self-closing.

Before:
```tsx
<Button
  type="submit"
  onClick={onSubmit}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  data-test-id="check-icon"
  style={{ padding: '0' }}
  isDisabled={isDisabled}
>
  <CheckIcon />
</Button>
```

After:
```tsx
<Button
  type="submit"
  onClick={onSubmit}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  data-test-id="check-icon"
  style={{ padding: '0' }}
  isDisabled={isDisabled}
  icon={<CheckIcon />}
/>
```

The `CheckIcon` import is still needed (it's now used in the `icon` prop), so no import cleanup is required.

